<poml>
    <task>
        Compare planned vs actual trajectory and analyze deviations in robotics logs.
        <stepwise-instructions>
            <list>
                <item>
                    Verify that the robolog file exists at the path: {{robolog_path}}.
                </item>
                <item>
                    If time filtering is requested ({{has_time_filter}} is true), use the start_seconds={{start_seconds}} and end_seconds={{end_seconds}} parameters when calling query_topic_messages to filter the data to the specified time window.
                </item>
                <item>
                    Use Bagel's `read_metadata` function to get basic information about the log and identify available topics.
                </item>
                <item>
                    Use Bagel's `describe_topics` function to identify topics containing planned trajectory data (look for topics like mission_waypoint, trajectory_setpoint, position_setpoint, etc.) and actual trajectory data (vehicle_local_position, vehicle_global_position, etc.).
                </item>
                <item>
                    Use Bagel's `query_topic_messages` function to extract planned trajectory data using SQL queries like:
                    - "SELECT timestamp_seconds, x, y, z, yaw FROM mission_waypoint ORDER BY timestamp_seconds"
                    - "SELECT timestamp_seconds, x, y, z, yaw FROM trajectory_setpoint ORDER BY timestamp_seconds"
                    - "SELECT timestamp_seconds, x, y, z, yaw FROM position_setpoint ORDER BY timestamp_seconds"
                </item>
                <item>
                    Use Bagel's `query_topic_messages` function to extract actual trajectory data using SQL queries like:
                    - "SELECT timestamp_seconds, x, y, z, vx, vy, vz, yaw, pitch, roll FROM vehicle_local_position ORDER BY timestamp_seconds"
                    - "SELECT timestamp_seconds, x, y, z, vx, vy, vz, yaw, pitch, roll FROM vehicle_global_position ORDER BY timestamp_seconds"
                </item>
                <item>
                    Calculate trajectory comparison metrics:
                    - Position errors: cross-track error, along-track error, 3D position error, altitude error
                    - Velocity errors: speed error, direction error, velocity vector error
                    - Timing errors: time delay, waypoint arrival time differences
                    - Path following performance: path deviation statistics, waypoint accuracy, path completion percentage
                    - Flight efficiency: actual vs planned distance, energy efficiency, smoothness analysis
                </item>
                <item>
                    Identify trajectory deviations and their causes:
                    - Large position errors (&gt; threshold)
                    - Sudden direction changes
                    - Altitude deviations
                    - Speed violations
                    - Wind effects (if wind data available)
                    - Control system delays
                    - Waypoint sequencing issues
                    - Obstacle avoidance maneuvers
                </item>
                <item>
                    Generate visualization descriptions for:
                    - 2D trajectory comparison (planned vs actual paths)
                    - 3D trajectory comparison with altitude profiles
                    - Error analysis plots (position, velocity, timing errors)
                    - Performance metrics and statistics
                </item>
                <item>
                    Create a comprehensive comparison summary in JSON format with:
                    - Summary statistics (analysis duration, waypoints, samples, completion percentage)
                    - Position errors (mean, max, cross-track, altitude errors)
                    - Velocity errors (speed, direction errors)
                    - Waypoint accuracy (arrival positions, timing errors)
                    - Deviation events (timestamps, types, magnitudes, causes)
                    - Performance indicators (smoothness, responsiveness, accuracy)
                    - Recommendations for improvement
                </item>
            </list>
        </stepwise-instructions>
    </task>
</poml>